
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `dd-list` baraye namayesh dadan dastgah-haye disk va partition-haye mojud dar system estefade mishavad. In dastoor be shoma komak mikonad ta etela'ati dar mored disk-haye sakht, SSD-ha, USB drive-ha, va digar vast-haye zakhire-sazi be dast avarid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `dd-list`  --> 📜 Namayesh hameye disk-ha va partition-ha ba etela'ate asasi.
    🔹 `dd-list --json`  --> 📦 Khuruji ra be shekl JSON namayesh midahad baraye barname-nevisi.
    🔹 `dd-list --scsi`  --> 🔩 Namayesh etela'ate SCSI baraye disk-ha.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ dd-list

    🔹 Namayesh listi az hameye disk-ha va partition-ha.

    $ dd-list --json

    🔹 Khuruji dar format JSON baraye estefade dar script-ha va barname-ha.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ dd-list | grep /dev/sda

    🔹 In dastoor natije-ye `dd-list` ra filter mikonad ta etela'at marbut be disk `/dev/sda` ra namayesh dahad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `dd-list` command is used to display the available disk devices and partitions on the system. It helps you to retrieve information about hard drives, SSDs, USB drives, and other storage media.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `dd-list`  --> 📜 Show all disks and partitions with basic information.
    🔹 `dd-list --json`  --> 📦 Display the output in JSON format for programming purposes.
    🔹 `dd-list --scsi`  --> 🔩 Show SCSI information for disks.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ dd-list

    🔹 Displays a list of all disks and partitions.

    $ dd-list --json

    🔹 Output in JSON format for use in scripts and applications.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ dd-list | grep /dev/sda

    🔹 This command filters the output of `dd-list` to show information related to the `/dev/sda` disk.
